      HERITAGE OF ZURK III: "The Moonbeam"                                      In this yet-to-be completed conclusion to the HOZ series, the adventurer,       now promoted to Guildmaster, finds himself awake in his home, with Maithe       still sleeping.                                                                 END                                                                             He wonders....should he show her his world? Or will her pure simplicity be      corrupted by it? He decides to show her part of it. After a humorous            explanation to his mother, the Guildmaster and Maithe once again                END                                                                             find themselves back in her father's land, King Eldor. Herein they resolve      to find their way to the Mythical Moonshadow Garden, of which he once saw       a brief image in an earlier quest, where he found a rose to calm Maithe's       troubled heart...                                                               END                                                                             Only in this garden is it said can be found the legendary power of the          moonbeam, the source of continuity between worlds, therein to build an          eternal bridge binding their two worlds.                                        END                                                                             But as they arrive in the center of the garden and behold the moonbeam, the     Guildmaster sees one final gateway. One final doorway.                          END                                                                             Maithe looks at him and nods. The guildmaster walks through....                 END                                                                             In the grand ultimate finale of all twelve stories, the Guildmaster has         all his questions answered at last. His destiny is complete.                    FINISH                                                                          